"***Question 1: \"How likely is it that Bond will escape from Blofeld?\"*** Not very likely\nBlofeld has two men with guns pointed at Bond, and they have tied him up. It is unlikely that he will be able to escape from this situation.\n\n***Question 2: \"How suspenseful do you find this passage to be?\"*** Very suspenseful\nThis passage creates a tense and suspenseful atmosphere by highlighting the danger that Bond is in and the attempts of Blofeld to capture him. The reader is on edge as Bond tries to find a way to escape from his captors. The description of the large bird crashing into the wall and the large ugly man pointing a gun at Bond also adds to the suspense."